{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "05", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "14", "M": "20", "S": "31"}}, "news": [{"title": "Nearly 69% of latest Sec 39A proposals in Bardez", "para": "The TCP department processed proposals for 88,249 sqm of land under Section 39A, with the state government approving 34,527 sqm and recommending another 53,722 sqm for public scrutiny. Bardez dominates land conversion, accounting for nearly 69% of the total area, with significant proposals in Tivim and Nadora. These approvals are subject to departmental clearances and pending court litigations.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/nearly-69-of-latest-sec-39a-proposals-in-bardez/131528719?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-2628074/131528719.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "High-level meet paves way for regularisation of Ulhasnagar properties", "para": "Maharashtra government is set to regularize unauthorized properties in Ulhasnagar built before 2011, a move benefiting lakhs. Occupants will now pay only 5% of the Ready Reckoner value for ownership, a significant reduction. A special task force will expedite the process, issuing Property Cards and resolving decades-old land disputes.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/high-level-meet-paves-way-for-regularisation-of-ulhasnagar-properties/131527595?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-13822/131527595.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Pay for traffic jams you create: Ahmedabad civic body's message to developers", "para": "Ahmedabad is introducing a new traffic policy. Developers will now pay for the congestion their projects cause. A traffic impact assessment will be mandatory for large commercial developments. Building ratings will assess environmental and community impact. Malls and offices must share private parking. Penalties for violations are significant. This aims to improve traffic flow and road safety across the city.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/ahmedabads-developers-face-traffic-congestion-costs-under-new-civic-policy/131527360?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-148918/131527360.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}